### Multi-Data-Store Route Qualifiers Testing
### This file demonstrates data store routing with route qualifiers (districtId and schoolYear)
### Make sure to deploy with the multi-data-store configuration configuration first

@configPort = 8081
@dmsPort = 8080
@sysAdminId = DmsConfigurationService
@sysAdminSecret = ValidClientSecret1234567890!Abcd

### Variables for testing
@districtId1 = 255901
@districtId2 = 255902
@schoolYear1 = 2024
@schoolYear2 = 2025

### ============================================================================
### STEP 1: Get Access Token from Configuration Service
### ============================================================================

### Get token for Configuration Service
# @name configTokenRequest
POST http://localhost:{{configPort}}/connect/token
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

client_id={{sysAdminId}}
&client_secret={{sysAdminSecret}}
&grant_type=client_credentials
&scope=edfi_admin_api/full_access

###
@configToken = {{configTokenRequest.response.body.access_token}}


### ============================================================================
### STEP 2: Create Vendor
### ============================================================================

### Create a new vendor
# @name createVendor
POST http://localhost:{{configPort}}/v2/vendors
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: bearer {{configToken}}

{
    "company": "Multi-District Test Vendor",
    "contactName": "Test Admin",
    "contactEmailAddress": "admin@testdistrict.edu",
    "namespacePrefixes": "uri://ed-fi.org,uri://testdistrict.edu"
}

###
@vendorLocation={{createVendor.response.headers.location}}

### Retrieve the vendor so that we can extract the Id
# @name getVendor
GET {{vendorLocation}}
Authorization: bearer {{configToken}}

###
@vendorId={{getVendor.response.body.id}}


### ============================================================================
### STEP 3: Create Data Stores with Route Contexts
### ============================================================================

### Create Data Store 1 - District 255901, School Year 2024
# @name createDataStore1
POST http://localhost:{{configPort}}/v2/dataStores
Authorization: bearer {{configToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "dataStoreType": "District",
  "name": "District 255901 - School Year 2024",
  "connectionString": "host=dms-postgresql;port=5432;username=postgres;password=abcdefgh1!;database=edfi_datamanagementservice_d255901_sy2024;"
}

###
@dataStore1Id = {{createDataStore1.response.body.id}}

### Create Route Context for Data Store 1 - districtId
# @name createRouteContext1A
POST http://localhost:{{configPort}}/v2/dataStoreContexts
Authorization: bearer {{configToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "dataStoreId": {{dataStore1Id}},
  "contextKey": "districtId",
  "contextValue": "{{districtId1}}"
}

### Create Route Context for Data Store 1 - schoolYear
# @name createRouteContext1B
POST http://localhost:{{configPort}}/v2/dataStoreContexts
Authorization: bearer {{configToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "dataStoreId": {{dataStore1Id}},
  "contextKey": "schoolYear",
  "contextValue": "{{schoolYear1}}"
}


### ============================================================================
### Create Data Store 2 - District 255901, School Year 2025
# @name createDataStore2
POST http://localhost:{{configPort}}/v2/dataStores
Authorization: bearer {{configToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

